  To Load Documentation Graph into Neo4j

  python scripts/docs_to_neo4j.py --clear --apply

  This will create:
  - 112 Document nodes
  - 217 RELATES_TO relationships
  - Category groupings

  You can then query documentation relationships:
  // Find all docs about relationships
  MATCH (d:Document) WHERE 'relationships' IN d.tags RETURN d

  // Find docs updated in last 30 days
  MATCH (d:Document) WHERE d.updated > date() - duration('P30D') RETURN d

  // Find documentation dependency graph
  MATCH (d:Document)-[:RELATES_TO]->(related) RETURN d.title, related.title
